Actually, the error `Index signature for type 'string' is missing in type 'ErrorBoundaryProps'` might be because `React.Component` props type `P` is expected to sometimes have an index signature depending on the version of `@types/react`. But usually, `P` doesn't need it. The error `Readonly<ErrorBoundaryProps>` mismatch is the main thing.

```tsx
export class ErrorBoundary extends React.Component<ErrorBoundaryProps, ErrorBoundaryState> {
  // REMOVE THESE:
